Abdul Wadud Prince Following at Programming Hero 2mo 2 months ago


Products are the major source of revenue for any company. The things that make the product better and stand out more are its features. A product always has some features that make it unique and special from others.

The importance of the features of any product can also cause psychological effects on the customer which can be both positive and negative. If it's positive then everybody would want it but if it's negative then everybody absolutely hates it, it's as simple as that.

So apart from all this psychology stuff, why really are the features important?

In order to know the answer, let's dive right into the backend of the product itself.



Whenever a product is launched, the customers look deeply into its features and decide how helpful or needy they actually are of these features. And these factors can directly change the end result and the future of the product as well as its value.

Great and unique features can bring value to the product and can be very beneficial for the organization when launched. Features and products when to bring great value and are well welcomed by the customers, they also start to trust the company as well. These can be really beneficial for the future of the company.



No matter what type of product you are launching or selling to the customers, a good marketing pitch can really put the product into the top tier. But a good marketing pitch should always connect well with the product and it all comes back to the features of the very product. So it really doesnt matter how much a company gives effort or spends money on marketing in the end it all comes down to the very features and the feature functionality of the product.



The features of the product play a very important in the psychology of the customers. If they find it useful, they are going to tell others about it. You can call it some sort of free marketing or advertisement. These can not only make the product itself a great success but can also generate a great amount of positive feedback for the company.



Features literally determine how good or successful the product is going to be. These features should be rather useful and unique; otherwise, most customers might take them as something totally useless. Hence, it can make the whole product a failure and can end with a huge loss for the company itself.

#Features #product #psychology

Sumiya Shajuti Following Sr. Job Placement Executive at Programming Hero || Helping Recruiters and HR by establishing worldwide connections to get skilled Developers completely free of cost. 2mo 2 months ago


Everyone has expectations, especially when they join a company. Developers are no different, they also have certain expectations whenever they join a company. It might be somewhat different from others, there are going to be some expectations for sure.

Most of the expectations of the developers are related to the job and it is rather common as most developers really want to advance their career to a greater level while also improving their skillset.

So, what exactly are the expectations?



Being technically competent can be one of the biggest expectations a developer could have. It ensures that they really know how to program and actually solve a problem. While problem-solving is the basic requirement of being a great developer, sadly most developers nowadays dont possess such traits.

So after joining a company most developers want to prove their technical competence and show how well they can solve a particular problem. These things can not only build the confidence level of the developer but also increases their hunger to learn and master something new.



No matter how you look at it, everyone should keep on learning. And everyone can learn anything from anyone. It really doesn't matter if that person is your junior or senior, you can always and definitely learn something new from them.

Whether the developer has no experience or not, that person might know something that others might not. These simple things can make them want to teach others the things they know while gaining some valuable knowledge or feedback from the really experienced people in the workplace.

Practicing such things will definitely create a healthy and friendly work environment where every single developer can improve their skill set while giving their very best.



Having and working with a great and friendly team is a dream of every developer. And no matter how you look at it, this kind of team can openly promote learning and increases the confidence level of every single developer. Team collaboration can not only help developers build a great and rich feature-packed project but can also teach each great thing while pushing their very limits.



Whenever a developer joins a company, expectation plays a very important role in how they are going to perform. If they get what they expected, you can definitely expect some great things from them otherwise, they are just going to work like some industry robots.
#developer #work #job #experience #career #learning
